# Clerk Billing (B2C SaaS)

Subscriptions and payments use **Clerk Billing** (B2C). Plans and features are configured in the [Clerk Dashboard](https://dashboard.clerk.com); do not duplicate billing state in app code except for UX gating aligned with Clerk.

Billing is **beta**—pin `@clerk/nextjs` and `clerk-js` versions per [Clerk pinning docs](https://clerk.com/docs/pinning.md) to reduce breaking changes.

## Canonical identifiers

Use **only** these slugs when checking plans or features (match Dashboard exactly):

**Plans**

- `free_user`
- `pro`

**Features**

- `ai_flashcard_generation`
- `unlimited_decks`
- `three_deck_limit`

Do not invent alternate plan or feature names in code.

## Pricing UI

- Use Clerk’s `<PricingTable />` from `@clerk/nextjs` on a **dedicated pricing page** (recommended pattern).
- Compose surrounding layout with **shadcn** components from `src/components/ui/` (e.g. layout wrappers, buttons for nav)—do not add non-shadcn UI libraries for elements shadcn provides.

## Server-side access checks

Use `has()` from `auth()` for routes, server components, and server actions that must enforce entitlements (especially mutations and anything that could be abused if only hidden in the UI).

```typescript
import { auth } from "@clerk/nextjs/server";

const { has } = await auth();

const isPro = has({ plan: "pro" });
const canUseAi = has({ feature: "ai_flashcard_generation" });
```

Enforce limits that map to features (e.g. deck counts, AI generation) in **server actions** via `has()` plus existing `db/queries` helpers—never rely on client-only checks for authorization.

## Client-side conditional UI

Use `<Show>` from `@clerk/nextjs` when conditionally rendering UI by plan or feature, with a `fallback` when the user lacks access.

```tsx
import { Show } from "@clerk/nextjs";

<Show
  when={{ plan: "pro" }}
  fallback={<p>Pro plan required.</p>}
>
  {/* Pro-only UI */}
</Show>

<Show
  when={{ feature: "ai_flashcard_generation" }}
  fallback={/* upgrade CTA using shadcn Button */}
>
  {/* AI generation UI */}
</Show>
```

## Relationship to auth and data rules

- **Clerk auth** still identifies the user; **billing** gates product capabilities. Combine `userId` / `ownerId` checks with `has()` where both apply (e.g. user must own the deck *and* have the feature to run AI on it).
